# Kwery Order Book Analysis

## Available Tools

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `polymarket_orderbook` | Polymarket CLOB bid/ask depth history |
| `kalshi_orderbook` | Kalshi binary market order book history |
| `polymarket_snapshots` | Point-in-time Polymarket book snapshots |
| `kalshi_snapshots` | Point-in-time Kalshi book snapshots |

## Spread Analysis

`spread = best_ask - best_bid`
`spread_pct = spread / mid_price * 100`

- <0.5% = liquid, safe for large orders
- 0.5-2% = moderate, use limit orders
- >2% = illiquid, expect significant slippage

## Depth Imbalance Signal

Sum bid sizes vs ask sizes across top N levels:
`imbalance = bid_depth / (bid_depth + ask_depth)`

- >0.6 = more buy-side pressure -> bullish signal
- <0.4 = more sell-side pressure -> bearish signal
- 0.4-0.6 = balanced book, no directional bias

## Slippage Estimation

Use `depth=50` to walk the full book for large-order slippage:
```
polymarket_orderbook(symbol="BTC", depth=50, limit=1)
```
Walk bid/ask levels until cumulative size >= order size, then compute VWAP fill price.

## Tier Limits

Free 7d - Pro 14d - Business 31d
Cost: 50 base + 4/row (polymarket), 50 base + 3/row (kalshi)
